decks.notes: The main idea behind this deck is to ramp up your mana quickly using cards like Arboreal Grazer and Amulet of Vigor, in order to take advantage of Primeval Titan's powerful ability to search your library for lands. By using cards like Green Sun's Zenith and Scapeshift, you can quickly assemble a lethal amount of lands, triggering Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle's ability to deal massive damage to your opponent. This deck relies on a powerful land combo to quickly overwhelm your opponent and secure a victory.

This Esper Control deck focuses on disrupting opponents with counterspells and hand disruption, while utilizing powerful creatures like Boggart Trawler and Ketramose, the New Dawn to control the board. Using cards like Thought Scour and Unearth to maximize value, the deck aims to outvalue the opponent while maintaining control of the game. With a mix of removal, disruption, and card advantage, the deck is designed to grind out wins through efficient play and careful resource management.

The main focus of this Esper Control deck is to disrupt and control the opponent's game plan through a combination of counterspells, removal, and card advantage. By utilizing cards like Counterspell, Force of Negation, Fatal Push, and Nihil Spellbomb, the deck aims to maintain board control and prevent the opponent from executing their strategy effectively. Additionally, the inclusion of creatures like Murktide Regent and Abhorrent Oculus provides a win condition for the deck, allowing it to close out the game once the opponent has been adequately controlled. The deck also includes some card draw and recursion to maintain consistency and outvalue the opponent.
